First observe that by separation of variables

\[
x^2\,\frac{dy}{dx}=y
\;\Longrightarrow\;
\frac{dy}{y}=\frac{dx}{x^2}
\;\Longrightarrow\;
\ln|y|=-\frac1x+K
\;\Longrightarrow\;
y=C\,e^{-1/x}\quad(C=e^K)
\]

as given.

To find the constant \(C\) so that \(y(1)=2/e\), plug in \(x=1\), \(y=2/e\):

\[
\frac{2}{e}
  \;=\;
y(1)
  \;=\;C\,e^{-1/1}
  \;=\;\frac{C}{e}
\quad\Longrightarrow\quad
C=2.
\]

Hence the particular solution through \(\bigl(1,\tfrac2e\bigr)\) is

\[
\boxed{\,y(x)=2\,e^{-1/x}\,.}
\]
